<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="105" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,1476,2043]" pageId="15" pageNumber="105">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1477,1503]" pageId="15" pageNumber="105">Remarks</emphasis>
: This species was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Calvert, P. P." box="[660,823,1476,1503]" pageId="15" pageNumber="105" pagination="73 - 280" refId="ref11549" refString="Calvert, P. P. (1909) Contributions to a knowledge of the Odonata of the Neotropical region, exclusive of Mexico and Central America. Annals of the Carnegie Museum, 6 (3), 73 - 280." type="journal article" year="1909">Calvert (1909)</bibRefCitation>
based on a male collected in Coroico (
<collectingCountry box="[1251,1339,1476,1503]" name="Bolivia" pageId="15" pageNumber="105">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
), including an illustration of cerci in dorsolateral view. 
<bibRefCitation author="Sjostedt, Y." box="[677,848,1512,1539]" pageId="15" pageNumber="105" pagination="1 - 54" refId="ref12124" refString="Sjostedt, Y. (1918) Wissenschaftliche Ergbnisse der Swedischen Entomologischen Reise des Herrn Dr. A. Roman in Amazonas 1914 - 1915. 1, Odonata. Arkiv vor Zoologi, 11 (15), 1 - 54." type="journal article" year="1918">Sjöstedt (1918)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName box="[968,1119,1513,1538]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="15" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="speciosum">
<emphasis box="[968,1119,1513,1538]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="105">H. speciosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on a single male from 
<collectingCountry box="[151,202,1549,1575]" name="Peru" pageId="15" pageNumber="105">Peru</collectingCountry>
and illustrated cerci in dorsolateral view, as well as color pattern of abdomen in dorsal view. 
<bibRefCitation author="Williamson, E. B." box="[1226,1436,1548,1575]" pageId="15" pageNumber="105" pagination="1 - 88" refId="ref12284" refString="Williamson, E. B. (1919) Results of the University of Michigan - Williamson expedition to Colombia, 1916 - 17. IV. Notes on species of the genus Heteragrion Selys with descriptions of new species (Odonata). Occasional Papers of the Museum of Zoology, University of Michigan, 68, 1 - 88. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 14454" type="journal article" year="1919">Williamson (1919)</bibRefCitation>
illustrated color pattern of head and posterior lobe of prothorax of 
<taxonomicName authority=", De Marmels (1987)" authorityName=", De Marmels" authorityYear="1987" box="[883,1281,1584,1611]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="15" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavidorsum">
<emphasis box="[883,1050,1585,1611]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="105">H. flavidorsum</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="De Marmels, J." box="[1063,1281,1584,1611]" pageId="15" pageNumber="105" pagination="225 - 238" refId="ref11626" refString="De Marmels, J. (1987) On the type specimens of some neotropical Megapodagrionidae, with a description of Heteragrion pemon spec. nov. and Oxystigma caerulans spec. nov. from Venezuela (Zygoptera). Odonatologica, 16 (3), 225 - 238." type="journal article" year="1987">De Marmels (1987)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
examined the 
<typeStatus box="[151,249,1620,1646]" pageId="15" pageNumber="105">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[287,438,1621,1646]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="15" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="speciosum">
<emphasis box="[287,438,1621,1646]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="105">H. speciosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and illustrated cerci and coloration pattern of head and thorax, arriving at the conclusion that 
<taxonomicName box="[199,349,1657,1682]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="15" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="speciosum">
<emphasis box="[199,349,1657,1682]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="105">H. speciosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", De Marmels" authorityYear="1987" box="[609,776,1657,1683]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="15" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavidorsum">
<emphasis box="[609,776,1657,1683]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="105">H. flavidorsum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Here, we report this species for 
<collectingCountry box="[1139,1252,1656,1682]" name="Colombia" pageId="15" pageNumber="105">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, from 
<collectingRegion country="Colombia" name="Putumayo" pageId="15" pageNumber="105">Putumayo Department</collectingRegion>
. Some important diagnostic characters of this species are the male cerci lacking a ventrobasal convexity (
<figureCitation box="[198,288,1728,1755]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1862,1887]" captionTargetBox="[353,1234,776,1843]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[353,1234,776,1843]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 9. Male cerci: H. demarmelsi: Leticia, Amazonas (A) dorsal view (B) mediodorsal view (C) lateral view. Heteragrion erythrogastrum: Union Panamericana, Chocó (D) dorsal view (E) mediodorsal view (F) lateral view. Heteragrion flavidorsum: PNN Churumbelos, Putumayo (G) dorsal view (H) mediodorsal view (I) lateral view. VbC: Ventro basal convexity." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3415717" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3415717/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="105">Fig. 9H</figureCitation>
) and provided with a very short middle process (
<figureCitation box="[853,921,1728,1755]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1862,1887]" captionTargetBox="[353,1234,776,1843]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[353,1234,776,1843]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 9. Male cerci: H. demarmelsi: Leticia, Amazonas (A) dorsal view (B) mediodorsal view (C) lateral view. Heteragrion erythrogastrum: Union Panamericana, Chocó (D) dorsal view (E) mediodorsal view (F) lateral view. Heteragrion flavidorsum: PNN Churumbelos, Putumayo (G) dorsal view (H) mediodorsal view (I) lateral view. VbC: Ventro basal convexity." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3415717" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3415717/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="105">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
G–H). The females of this species was so far unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="106" pageId="15" pageNumber="105" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,1476,2043]" pageId="15" pageNumber="105">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,504,1800,1827]" pageId="15" pageNumber="105">Description of the female</emphasis>
: 
<emphasis box="[521,582,1801,1827]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="105">Head</emphasis>
: mainly brown, labrum dark brown with orange central spot, clypeus dark brown, black crossbar at level of antenna, antennal base dark brown, brown crossbar at level of ocelli and a black crossbar along posterior margin, rear of head brown (
<figureCitation box="[748,838,1872,1899]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1465,1490]" captionTargetBox="[359,1216,453,1446]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[359,1227,453,1446]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Face color pattern: H. calendulum (taken from Bota-Sierra &amp; Novelo-Gutierrez 2017): (A) male Pueblo Rico, Risaralda (B) female Pueblo Rico, Risaralda. Heteragrion demarmelsi: (C) male Leticia, Amazonas (D) female Leticia, Amazo- nas. Heteragrion erythrogastrum: (E) male Union Panamericana, Chocó (F) female Union Panamericana, Chocó. Heteragrion flavidorsum: (G) male PNN Churumbelos, Putumayo (H) female PNN Churumbelos, Putumayo. H. inca: (I) male Puerto Legui- zamo, Putumayo (J) female Puerto Leguizamo, Putumayo." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3415709" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3415709/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="105">Fig. 5H</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,1476,2043]" lastBlockId="16.[151,1437,153,395]" lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="106" pageId="15" pageNumber="105">
<emphasis box="[199,313,1909,1935]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="105">Prothorax</emphasis>
: anterior lobe black with gray central spot, middle lobe dark gray with two black dorsal spots, posterior lobe black with pale brown posterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[700,803,1944,1971]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1180,1205]" captionTargetBox="[355,1230,190,1152]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[349,1237,181,1161]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 16. Female structures: H. tatama: PNN Tatamá, Risaralda (A) S9–10 lateral view (B) S9–10 ventral view (C) intersternite. Heteragrion demarmelsi: Leticia, Amazonas (D) male habitus (E) female habitus. Heteragrion angustipenne: Mocoa, Putumayo (F) female habitus. Heteragrion flavidorsum: PNN Churumbelos, Putumayo (G) female habitus. Heteragrion demarmelsi: Leticia, Amazonas (H) male thorax dorsal (I) female thorax dorsal. Heteragrion angustipenne: Mocoa, Putumayo (J) female throax dorsal. Heteragrion flavidorsum: PNN Churumbelos, Putumayo (K) female thorax dorsal." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3253608/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="105">Fig. 16K</figureCitation>
), dorsal plate of intersternite with swollen anterior corner (
<figureCitation box="[160,259,1980,2007]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1334,1359]" captionTargetBox="[378,1207,314,1306]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[370,1218,309,1314]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 14. Female structures: H. erythrogastrum: Union Panamericana, Chocó (A) S9–10 lateral view (B) S9–10 ventral view (C) intersternite. Heteragrion flavidorsum: PNN Churumbelos, Putumayo (D) S9–10 lateral view (E) S9–10 ventral view (F) intersternite. H. demarmelsi: Leticia, Amazonas (G) S9–10 lateral view (H) S9–10 ventral view (I) intersternite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3253604/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="105">Fig. 14F</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis box="[279,413,1981,2007]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="105">Pterothorax</emphasis>
: mesepisternum pale brown with black middorsal line and black antehumeral stripe, mesepimeron gray with black stripe, mesinfraespisternum gray with black spot, metepisternum pale brown with black stripe, metepimeron pale yellow, metinfraepisternum pale yellow with black spot (
